. \"Harbin in comparative perspective.\" ''Urban History'' 37.1 (2010): 136\u2013149.\n* Guins, George C. \"Russians in Manchuria.\" ''Russian Review'' 2.2 (1943): 81\u201387. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/125255 Online] [https://www.jstor.org/stable/pdf/j.ctt1zxsk34.29.pdf excerpt]\n* Lahusen, Thomas. \"A place called Harbin: reflections on a centennial.\" ''China Quarterly'' 154 (1998): 400\u2013410.\n* Meyer, Mike, \"Manchuria Under Ice\", ''Departures Magazine'', Nov/Dec 2006, 292\u2013297\n* Xie, Liou, et al. \"Harbin: A rust belt city revival from its strategic position.\" ''Cities'' 58 (2016): 26\u201338. [https://www.research.manchester.ac.uk/portal/files/54542734/FULL_TEXT.PDF Online]\n*Zissermann, Lenore Lamont, ''Mitya's Harbin; Majesty and Menace'', Book Publishers Network, 2016, {{ISBN|978-1-940598-75-8}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links|Harbin}}\n*[http://www.harbin.gov.cn/ Harbin Government website]\n*{{Britannica|254877}}\n*{{Wikivoyage-inline}}\n\n{{Harbin}}\n{{Heilongjiang topics}}\n{{Heilongjiang}}\n{{Metropolitan cities of the People's Republic of China}}\n{{Most populous cities in the People's Republic of China}}\n{{Provincial capitals of China}}\n{{Asian Games Host Cities}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Harbin| ]]\n[[Category:Cities in Heilongjiang]]\n[[Category:Provincial capitals in China]]\n[[Category:Songhua River]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Harbin (disambiguation)}}\n{{stack begin}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = {{raise|0.2em|Harbin}}\n| official_name                   = \n| native_name                     = {{lower|0.1em|\u54c8\u5c14\u6ee8\u5e02}}\n| native_name_lang = zh-Hans\n| other_name                      = \n| nicknames                        = Ice City, Oriental Paris, Oriental Moscow, The pearl on the swan's neck\n| settlement_type                 = [[Prefecture-level city|Prefecture-level]] & [[Sub-provincial city]]\n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline     